-- Israeli Probe Finds Mistakes Made in Decision-Making Before Flotilla Raid
-- Gwen Ackerman
-- 2010-07-12T14:12:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/israeli-probe-finds-mistakes-made-in-decision-making-before-flotilla-raid.html

          
          
             An Israeli army inquiry found
mistakes were made in the decision-making process ahead of a
naval commando raid on a Gaza Strip-bound aid flotilla that left
nine Turkish citizens dead, committee head Major General Giora
Eiland said in comments broadcast on Israel Army Radio.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Gwen Ackerman in Jerusalem at 
 gackerman@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        